  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d9a\u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The President's resignation to the speaker",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa has sent the letter of resignation from the post of President to Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena tonight (14).",
        "Mr. Gotabaya Rajapakse, who left the Colombo Fort Presidential Palace and stayed at a security post on the island due to the disturbing situation in the country, left for the Maldives on the 12th with his wife and two security guards in a special plane of the Air Force. He left the Maldives and arrived in Singapore this afternoon.",
        "Parliamentary sources say that the President's resignation letter is being investigated by the Speaker and legal departments.",
        "A special meeting of the Committee on Parliamentary Affairs is scheduled to be held tomorrow morning at the Parliament Complex under the chairmanship of the Speaker and the necessary decisions regarding the appointment of a new President will be taken there, said the sources.",
        "The resignation letter sent by President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa to the speaker reads as follows."
      ],
